net.hudup.core.data

Class ObjectPair<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.ObjectPair<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of key.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class ObjectPair<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cloneable
    This class is the pair of key and value. Key is an object indicating anything but value is double number. The key is unusual and so this class is mainly used for sorting objects (as keys) by their values (as double numbers).
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • sort

        public static <T> void sort(java.util.List<ObjectPair<T>> pairList,
                            int maxNumber,
                            boolean descending)
        Sorting the list of pairs. In fact, this method sorts keys (as objects) of pairs according to the associated values (as double numbers).
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of keys in pairs.
        Parameters:
        pairList - list of pairs to be sorted. This is an input and output parameter.
        maxNumber - the maximum number of pairs in the sorted list as result. If this number is smaller than the number of the original list, the final sorted list is truncated till to this number.
        descending - if true, the list is sorted according to descending order.
